A vintage 1950s propaganda poster style illustration depicting an overflowing mailbox exploding with hundreds of envelopes and papers scattered chaotically in the wind, set against a dramatic red, white and blue color palette. The mailbox is comically overstuffed, with letters spilling onto a suburban lawn. A single emphatic red "X" mark stamp hovers prominently in the composition. The scene has aged paper texture, halftone dot patterns, and faded patriotic bunting in the background, evoking mid-century American political ephemera with a satirical edge.
